      "name": {
        "en": "GST"
      },
      "title": {
        "en": "Goods and Services Tax"
      },
      "desc": {
        "en": "New Zealand's Goods and Services Tax (GST) is a consumption tax applied to\nmost goods and services sold in New Zealand. Introduced in 1986, it operates\nas a value-added tax collected at each stage of the supply chain. Businesses\nregistered for GST charge the tax on their sales and can claim back GST paid\non business purchases. The current standard rate is 15%."
      },
